'''Catherine Wilder Disher''' (born June 22, 1960)<ref>{{IMDb name|0228324}}</ref> is a [[Canadians|Canadian]] [[actress]] and [[voice actress]]. She has won two [[Gemini Awards]]: in 2005 for Best Actress for her role in the Canadian mini-series ''[[Snakes and Ladders (TV series)|Snakes and Ladders]]'',<ref>[http://www.cbc.ca/arts/story/2004/12/13/geminiawards041213.html CBC.ca]</ref> and in 2010 for her role in ''[[The Border (TV series)|The Border]]''. She was also nominated for her role as Dr. Natalie Lambert in the ''[[Forever Knight]]'' TV series.
==Career== {{BLP unsourced section|date=March 2015}} Disher graduated from the [[Phillips Exeter Academy]] in 1978 and later from the [[National Theatre School of Canada]] in [[Montreal]].
She had a supporting role on ''[[T. and T.]]'', the legal/action series starring [[Mr. T]], and had another supporting role in the second season of the ''[[War of the Worlds (TV series)|War of the Worlds]]'' series. From 1992 to 1996 she starred in ''[[Forever Knight]]'' and provided the voice of [[Jean Grey (Phoenix)|Jean Grey]] on the [[X-men The Animated Series|X-men]] from 1992-1997.<ref>{{cite web|title=The X-Men Episode Guide 3x12: 'Dark Phoenix Part I: Dazzled' |url=http://comicsalliance.com/the-x-men-episode-guide-3x12-dark-phoenix-part-i-dazzled/ |website=Comics Alliance |accessdate=2 October 2016 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161016144036/http://comicsalliance.com/the-x-men-episode-guide-3x12-dark-phoenix-part-i-dazzled/ |archivedate=16 October 2016 |df= }}</ref> She played Maggie Norton on the Canadian television series ''[[The Border (TV series)|The Border]]'' from 2008 to 2010 and provides additional voices on the [[PBS Kids]]/[[CBC Kids]] series ''[[Super WHY!]]''.
Apart from her work as an actor, Disher has done voice work for animated series and video games, such as [[Resident Evil 3]]<ref>{{cite web|title=CRIMSON HEAD ELDER Interview Catherine Disher|url=http://www.crimson-head.com/apps/podcast/podcast/327618|website=CRIMSON HEAD ELDER|accessdate=2 October 2016}}</ref> and [[Sailor Moon]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Finally, We Can End the Catherine Disher Saga...(And A Gemini Awards Update)|url=http://moon-chase.blogspot.ca/2009/11/finally-we-can-end-catherine-disher.html|website=moon-chase.blogspot.ca|accessdate=2 October 2016}}</ref> She also wrote one episode of the British-Canadian drama series ''[[The Campbells]]''.
Disher played Martha Tinsdale in a series of made-for-TV movie about [[The Good Witch]], alongside her X-men co-star [[Chris Potter (actor)|Chris Potter]]. She has continued the role on the television series ''[[Good Witch (TV series)|Good Witch]]''.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Dillard|first1=Mechele R.|title=GOOD WITCH 'Madame Mayor' Catherine Disher Almost Became a Zoologist! (Interview)|url=http://tvruckus.com/2015/04/10/good-witch-madame-mayor-catherine-disher-almost-became-a-zoologist-interview/|website=TVRuckus|accessdate=2 October 2016}}</ref>
==Personal life==
She was formerly married to her ''[[X-Men (TV series)|X-Men]]'' co-star [[Cedric Smith (actor)|Cedric Smith]], 17 years her senior, with whom she had a son, Darcy Montgomery Smith, in 1993.
